-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Cementos Lima, Pacasmayo, Volcan
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-02-08T21:48:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/peru-stocks-buenaventura-cementos-lima-pacasmayo-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a third session, falling
0.3 percent to 22,730.70. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid
0.4 percent to 2,859.56.  Mining and industrial stocks declined on investor concern
about delays in a solution to  Europe ’s debt crisis, said  Daniel Romero , an analyst at Lima-based investment fund NC&F
Inversiones SA.  Cementos Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASC1)  (CPACASC1 PE) plunged 11 percent to
6.08 soles after the Hochschild Group’s cement producer sold
shares in  New York  at the lower end of a projected range,
Inteligo SAB analyst Alessandra Bazan said. Cementos Lima SA
(CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest cement maker, fell 3.1
percent to 2.50 soles.   Edegel SA (EDE)  (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian
unit of  Spain ’s Endesa SA, dropped 2.1 percent to 1.90 soles.
 Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VCM\B)  (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc and
silver producer, declined for a third day, losing 1.7 percent to
3.47 soles.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the
country’s biggest precious-metals miner, fell for the fourth
time in five sessions, losing 1.5 percent to $41.65.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, jumped 4.9 percent to 64 centimos after sugar futures
rose to the highest price in more than a week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
